       It is also possible to specify the colour values of ffoorreeggrroouunndd,
       bbaacckkggrroouunndd, ccuurrssoorrCCoolloorr, ccuurrssoorrCCoolloorr22, ccoolloorrBBDD, ccoolloorrUULL
       as a number 0-15, as a convenient shorthand to reference the colour name of
       color0-color15.

       Note that --rrvv (""rreevveerrsseeVViiddeeoo:: TTrruuee"") simulates reverse video by
       always swapping the foreground/background colours.  This is in contrast to
       _x_t_e_r_m(1) where the colours are only swapped if they have not otherwise been
       specified.
       For example,

       rrxxvvtt --ffgg BBllaacckk --bbgg WWhhiittee --rrvv
              would yield White on Black, while on _x_t_e_r_m(1) it would yield
              Black on White.

EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTT
       rrxxvvtt sets the environment variables TTEERRMM, CCOOLLOORRTTEERRMM and CCOOLLOORRFFGGBBGG.  The
       environment variable WWIINNDDOOWWIIDD is set to the X window id number of the
       rrxxvvtt window and it also uses and sets the environment variable DDIISSPPLLAAYY
       to specify which display terminal to use.  rrxxvvtt uses the environment
       variables RRXXVVTTPPAATTHH and PPAATTHH to find XPM files.

FFIILLEESS
       //eettcc//uuttmmpp
              System file for login records.

       //uussrr//lliibb//XX1111//rrggbb..ttxxtt
              Color names.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _x_t_e_r_m(1), _s_h(1), _r_e_s_i_z_e(1), _X(1), _p_t_y(4), _t_t_y(4), _u_t_m_p(5)

       See rxvtRef.html rxvtRef.txt for detailed information on recognized
       escape sequences and menuBar syntax, etc.

BBUUGGSS
       Check the BUGS file for an up-to-date list.

       Cursor change support is not yet implemented.

       Click-and-drag doesn't work with X11 mouse report overriding.

       Graphics support is fairly crude.

FFTTPP LLOOCCAATTIIOONN
       rxvt-2.6.4.tar.gz can be found at the following ftp sites
       ftp://ftp.rxvt.org/pub/rxvt

